%N A131179 a(n) = if n mod 2 == 0 then n*(n+1)/2, otherwise (n-1)*n/2 + 1.
%C A131179 From _Wesley Ivan Hurt_, Jun 24 2024: (Start)
%C A131179 Fill an array with the natural numbers n = 1,2,... along diagonals in alternating 'down' and 'up' directions. For n > 0, a(n) is row 1 of the boustrophedon-style array (see example).
%C A131179 In general, row k is given by (1+t^2+(n-k)*(-1)^t)/2, t = n+k-1. Here, k=1, n>0. (End)
